ral criteria. These criteria include the following requirements:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Structure must have a not-for-profit designation</li>\r\n<li>Project must be specifically related to children (0-16 years of age)</li>\r\n<li>Grant must apply to actual implementation of an initiative and not to the association funding</li>\r\n<li>Project must be in line with long-term goals and have long-term durability</li>\r\n<li>Project must be based in one of the countries where the Foundation operates (<a href="http://www.fondation-bel.org/en/pdf/Countries%20where%20the%20Foundation%20operates.pdf">see the list of countries</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Selection and Project Follow-up Committee meets as many times as is necessary and at least before each Board of Directors meeting. Chaired by Antoine Fiévet, Bel\'s Foundation Board of Directors meets twice a year to give its final decision on which cases should be sponsored and to follow up on them.</p>\r\n<!--:-->', '<!--:fr-->Soumettre un projet<!--:--><!--:en-->Submit a project<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-18', '', '', '2012-07-12 16:22:51', '2012-07-12 15:22:51', '', 16, 'http://fondation-bel.draft.lu/16-revision-18/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
