s lesquels la Fondation intervient (<a href="http://www.fondation-bel.org/fr/pdf/Pays%20dans%20lesquels%20la%20fondation%20intervient.pdf" target="_blank">voir la liste des pays</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p style="text-align: left;">Le CSSP se réunit autant de fois que nécessaire, et au minimum avant chaque Conseil d’Administration. Présidé par Antoine Fiévet, Président Directeur Général du groupe Bel, le Conseil d’Administration de la <strong>Fondation</strong> se réunit quant à lui au minimum deux fois dans l\'année pour donner son avis final sur les dossiers à soutenir et pour suivre leur bonne exécution.</p><!--:--><!--:en--><p>The Bel Foundation\'s mission consist of supporting projects from associations based in countries all around the world.<br />\r\n<strong>Do you represent an association that works to improve children\'s well-being, </strong>and are you undertaking a project aimed at <strong>promoting a balanced diet ?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<div style="border: solid 2px #9B0;">\r\n<p align="center"><strong>Download <a href="http://www.fondation-bel.org/en/pdf/Bel_Foundation_Request_for_funding.doc">the application form</a> and send it back completed by email to the following address:</strong></p>\r\n<p align="center"><strong><a href="mailto:contact@fondation-bel.org">contact@fondation-bel.org</a></strong></p>\r\n<p align="center">Applications will be studied in the course of their receipt during July 2012<br />\r\nand till the week of September 10 at the latest.</p>\r\n<p align="center"><img src="http://www.fondation-bel.org/images/warning.jpg" alt="" width="19" height="16" align="absmiddle" /> No incomplete files will be considered.<img src="http://www.fondation-bel.org/images/warning.jpg" alt="" width="19" height="16" align="absmiddle" /></p>\r\n<p style="text-align: center;">\r\n</div>\r\n<p>Before going to the Foundation\'s Board of Directors, applications are pre-selected by the Selection and Project Follow-up Committee (CSSP) after being analyzed using several criteria. These criteria include the following requirements:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Structure must have a not-for-profit designation</li>\r\n<li>Project must be specifically related to children (0-16 years of age)</li>\r\n<li>Grant must apply to actual implementation of an initiative and not to the association funding</li>\r\n<li>Project must be in line with long-term goals and have long-term durability</li>\r\n<li>Project must be based in one of the countries where the Foundation operates (<a href="http://www.fondation-bel.org/en/pdf/Countries%20where%20the%20Foundation%20operates.pdf">see the list of countries</a>)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The Selection and Project Follow-up Committee meets as many times as is necessary and at least before each Board of Directors meeting. Chaired by Antoine Fiévet, Bel\'s Foundation Board of Directors meets twice a year to give its final decision on which cases should be sponsored and to follow up on them.</p>\r\n<!--:-->', '<!--:fr-->Soumettre un projet<!--:--><!--:en-->Submit a project<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '16-revision-26', '', '', '2012-07-12 16:28:42', '2012-07-12 15:28:42', '', 16, 'http://fondation-bel.draft.lu/16-revision-26/', 0, 'revision', '', 0) ; 
